Array
- to loop through an array just use for loop
- array indexes start from zero
- to access values within an array use the index
- example arr[0] gets the first value of the array "arr"
- can store any kind of data, even objects
- even multiple data type in the same array

Object
 - to loop through an object use for..in
 - it's gauranteed to loop through everything
 - for (const key in object)
   - needs to be const not let
   - let is a data type
   - const is needed so the for loop can know what they're looping is a key
   - using let can cause problems
   - let will cause it to read it as a string instead of an object
   - it will be unable to access anything

- to loop through an object's propeties
  - 1) loop through the object' keys first
  - 2) loop through the values in their keys
  
  TO ACCESS VALUES IF:
  IF EACH KEY HAS AN ARRAY OF VALUES 
  - 1) use for...in
  - 2) use for loop

   IF EACH KEY HAS AN OBJECT OF VALUES 
  - 1) use for...in
  - 2) use for...in